Qualifying Standards for World Masters Championships -Predictions

05 September 2018

1 SMF distribution

It looks like there is a bimodal distribution for men (200-330 and 330-450) and for women (120-180 and 180-250).

2 SMF trend over time

2.1 SMF trend over time by age category and gender

For some age categories for men there is slight downward trend from 2010 to 2018 in the SMF. For women it is an upward trend.

Comment: the separation of the lines for women does indicate that the SMF formula may not fit well for to womens data. Here there are more women since 2016, and the distance between the curves is similar 2016 to 2018.

2.2 Distributions of SMF in 2018 (with quantile 0.2)

The distributions of SMF differ across the age classes. In some age groups there is a bimodal distribution. The oldest age groups are shifted to the left (lower end). This can also be ssen by looking at the line for the 0.2 quantile of each distribution.

2.3 Quantile regression lines for SMF across time

Quantile regression lines (10, 20,30, 40, 50, 75 %) for men

Quantile regression lines (10, 20,30, 40, 50, 75 %) for women

2.4 Tables of participants, adjusting bodyweight for new weight categories

This indicates that the most pressure is in the younger age groups in the middle weight categories.
